==English==
===Etymology===
Arbitrary letters + ''-on'' (by analogy with '''[[cotton]]'''); the frequently heard claim that the word derives from abbreviations of '''[[New York]]''' ("NY") and '''[[London]]''' ("Lon") is a myth.

===Pronunciation===
*(''UK''): {{IPA|/ˈnaɪlɒn/}}, {{SAMPA|/"naIlQn/}}
*(''US''): nīʹlän, {{IPA|/ˈnaɪlɑːn/}}, {{SAMPA|/"naIlA:n/}}

===Rhymes===
*[[Rhymes:English:-aɪlɒn|-aɪlɒn]]

====Noun====
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-reg-both}}
#Originally, the [[DuPont]] company trade name for [[polyamide]], a [[copolymer]] whose molecules consist of alternating [[diamine]] and [[dicarboxylic acid]] [[monomer]]s bonded together; now generically used for this type of [[polymer]].
#(''usually in plural'' '''nylons''') A [[stocking]] originally fabricated from nylon; also used generically for any long, sheer stocking.

